Please refer to INSTALL for information on installing Vuurmuur.

Please look at INSTALL.DEBIAN for installing on Debian systems,
INSTALL.MANDRAKE for Mandrake, INSTALL.SUSE for SUSE Linux.

Other documentation is currently only available online. Please visit
http://vuurmuur.sourceforge.net/

A wiki site is available at http://vuurmuur.twc-net.com/tiki/
On the wiki a FAQ is also available.


Especially take a look at the QuickSetupGuide, written by Philippe
Baumgart, which will get you going with the configuration. The Guide
can be found here:
http://sourceforge.net/project/showfiles.php?group_id=114382&package_id=150383


Vuurmuur supports using IPTrafficVolume (http://iptrafficvolume.sourceforge.net/)
for keeping track of the traffic volume per interface. Please read this for
instructions for setting it up:
http://sourceforge.net/docman/display_doc.php?docid=26869&group_id=114382


For using Vuurmuur with the Portscan Attack Detector (http://www.cipherdyne.org/),
please read these instructions:
http://sourceforge.net/docman/display_doc.php?docid=25631&group_id=114382
